Fix the anvil worker pool killing its own workers.

Five related fixes to anvil-worker.el:

1. anvil-worker--server-file-stale-p probed the socket by re-expanding
   its basename against the *current* server-socket-dir.  The pool caches
   absolute socket paths at init; if the user customizes server-socket-dir
   later in init, every probe looks in the wrong directory, condemns the
   healthy worker, deletes its live socket, and orphans the daemon.
   Probe the cached path itself instead.

2. Workers are spawned with -Q and so bound their sockets in the default
   socket directory, not necessarily where the pool looks.  Propagate the
   pool-cached socket directory into the generated worker init file.

3. A worker still loading its init could be declared dead by the health
   timer and doubled by a same-named twin daemon; twins fight over one
   socket path.  Add anvil-worker-spawn-grace (45s) suppression.

4. Once that grace suppresses a health-timer respawn, the worker's
   recorded state is already dead.  Retry spawning on every dead tick,
   while continuing to log only state transitions; the grace period is
   the retry rate limiter.

5. An intentional pool kill/reset must not inherit stale spawn-grace
   timestamps.  Clear the grace table when killing the pool.

